✅ C Language Syllabus for Embedded Interviews
🎯 PRIORITY LEGEND: ⭐⭐⭐ = CRITICAL | ⭐⭐ = IMPORTANT | ⭐ = GOOD TO KNOW

✔ Syntax & Structure ⭐⭐⭐
C program structure, header files
Preprocessing → Compilation → Assembly → Linking
Object files, symbol tables
Static vs dynamic linking
Cross-compilation basics for embedded
Preprocessor directives (#include, #define, macros)

✔ Data Types
Integer sizes, signedness
char, ASCII, Unicode basics
float, double, precision issues
enum, typedef, struct, union

✔ Operators
Bitwise operators (very important)
Shift operators — logical vs arithmetic
Pre/post increment behavior

✔ Pointer Basics
Basics: pointer to int/char/float
Void pointer
Dangling pointer
Wild pointer
NULL pointer

✔ Multi-level & Special Pointers
Pointer to pointer
Double/triple pointers
Pointer to array vs array of pointers
Function pointers
Callback functions
Difference between ptr++ and ++ptr

✔ Arrays
Static & dynamic arrays
Multi-dimensional arrays

✔ Strings
strlen, strcpy, strncpy, strcmp, etc.

✔ Structures
Padding and alignment (very important)
Packing (#pragma pack)
Nested structures
Structure vs typedef struct

✔ Unions
Memory sharing
Use cases in embedded(To store register bits)
Difference between struct & union
Using bitfields to access hardware registers

✔ Function basics
Call by value vs call by reference
Inline vs normal functions

✔ Advanced
Recursion
Function pointers
Re-entrant functions
Static functions (internal linkage)
Storage classes (static, auto, extern, register)

✔ Memory Management
Stack vs Heap
malloc/calloc/realloc/free
Memory leaks & fragmentation
Segmentation faults
Memory alignment
Cache behavior
Cache-friendly coding
Locality of reference

✔ Bit operations ⭐⭐⭐ EXTREMELY IMPORTANT
Used for: audio codec registers, DSP control, I2C/SPI communication, audio format flags.
Set/clear/toggle/test a bit
Create bit masks
Extract high/low nibbles
Extract fields from registers
Rotate left/right

✔ Embedded System / Audio Specific C Concepts ⭐⭐⭐
Volatile keyword ⭐⭐⭐
Why needed for hardware registers (audio codec registers)
Why needed for ISRs (audio DMA interrupts)
Compiler optimization issues

✔ const vs volatile ⭐⭐⭐
✔ Memory-mapped I/O ⭐⭐⭐ (audio device registers)
✔ Endianness: big vs little ⭐⭐⭐ (audio data format conversion)
✔ Interrupt service routines (ISR) basics ⭐⭐⭐ (audio DMA callbacks)
✔ Bare-metal vs RTOS differences ⭐⭐
✔ DMA (Direct Memory Access) ⭐⭐⭐ (zero-copy audio buffer transfer)
